Presiding Pastor, Omega Fire Ministries Worldwide, Apostle Johnson Suleman has called on Nigerians to speak positive about the country on October 1 as Nigeria turns 59 tomorrow. According to him, Nigerians must be positive in their utterances about the country. He also said that Nigerians have been inflicted with selfish leaders and greedy politicians. The outspoken cleric said this in a post on his official Twitter page on Monday. “Nigeria is 59 tomorrow. Pls, let’s be positive in our utterances. Negativity has gotten us nowhere. Yes, we have been inflicted with selfish leaders and greedy politicians. “They will get their reward but we won’t verbally mutilate our nation anymore. Pls, speak positive tomorrow.” Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.